April 2, 2020

Dear Winslow Township Community:

The Perfecting Church operates a Mobile Food Pantry the first Saturday of each month at Winslow Township School No. 3, located at 131 Sicklerville Road, Sicklerville, NJ.

On Saturday, April 4, 2020 at 9:00 a.m., the Mobile Food Pantry will be giving food to families in the Winslow Township Community, in the School No. 3 parking lot.

If you are interested, you must subscribe to the Pantry Text Alert Service by texting HopeMobile (all one word) to the number 46786. If you have any questions, you may call Mrs. Angela Brown at (856) 817-6223.

Sincerely,

H. Major Poteat, Ed.D., Superintendent

post_text:
Dear Parents,
Starting Tuesday, March 17 through Tuesday, March 31st, all schools in the Winslow Township School District will be closed.

All students should be in school on Monday, March 16, 2020. Students will be asked to take home all of their textbooks and remove all personal items from their lockers.

More detailed information will be provided on Monday explaining how students will be able to access their lessons online or how to use the packets of information they will receive from their teachers.

Again, it is very important that all students are in school on Monday. Arrangements will be made with each school for those students who are home sick. In order for this transitional process to be effective, we must work together.

Thank you in advance for your continued support.

Respectfully,
H. Major Poteat, Ed.D., Superintendent

March 12, 2020

Dear Parent/Guardian:

In preparation for a possible public health related school closure due to the spread of the Coronavirus (COVID-19), the Winslow Township School District will have early dismissal days for students on March 17, 18, and 19, 2020. During this time, our teachers and administrators will have an opportunity to prepare plans for the provision of home instruction.

Please keep in mind, that schools will only close following a written directive by either the New Jersey Department of Health or the Camden County Department of Health.

Therefore, it is in the best interest of our staff and students that we have a preparedness plan in place if this occurs.

Thank you for your continued support.

Sincerely,

H. Major Poteat, Ed.D.
Superintendent

Tonya Dorsey & New Vision Scholarship Program

Winslow Township students are invited to apply for the Tonya Dorsey & New Vision Scholarship. This $500.00 scholarship has been established to provide scholarships to children, grades 4 through 11, who are pursuing admission to or continuance in an accredited institute of performing arts, and who have demonstrated a desire to pursue formal training.

Scholarship Opens: February 1st
Scholarship Closes: March 31st

Scholarship applications can be emailed to TonyaDorseyandNewVision@comcast.net or mailed to TDNV Scholarships, P.O. BOX 764, Turnersville NJ, 08012 between the aforementioned dates. Finalists will be notified in April and an interview/audition will be scheduled. For More information, please select the link below.
www.tdnvscholarships.org

post_text:
On Wednesday, August 14, 2019, the START Project will be hosting a webinar entitled, Let's Read Together! Tips to Make Story Time Fun and Frequent. The purpose of this webinar is to encourage parents and caregivers of young children (ages birth to 8 years old) to read with their children at home.

This one-hour webinar will provide tips to improve the efficacy of these sessions and to hopefully make them more enjoyable for both the parents and children so that story time will be a more common household event.

Please share information about this event with parents in your network. Professionals are welcome to attend as well.

Dear Winslow Township School District Community,
The Winslow Township Board of Health is excited to bring the Pediatric Mobile Services to our Community just in time for back-to-school! The Virtua Pediatric Mobile Services team provides a variety of services for children ages 0-7 years old.

If you know of anyone with children under the age of 7 who may be able to benefit from Free Lead, Developmental and or Dental Screenings please, feel free to stop by Winslow Township STAR Center during the days and times listed below. No appointment is necessary. If you have any questions about Virtua's Program, please call 609-304-0151.

100 ERIAL ROAD
SICKLERVILLE, NJ 08081

Wednesday August 28th (9 am - 1 pm) Free Developmental Screening
Thursday August 29th (9 am - 1 pm) Free Dental Screenings

Dear Parent/Guardian:

According to State Law, our school district calendar must have at least one-hundred eighty (180) student days. This year it has been necessary to close schools five days (January 4, January 5, March 8, March 21, and March 22) due to inclement weather. In order to make up these days, the Winslow Township School Board has approved the following make up days:

Monday, April 2, 2018 Full School Day for Staff & Students
Tuesday, April 3, 2018 Full School Day for Staff & Students
Wednesday, April 4, 2018 Full School Day for Staff & Students
Thursday, April 5, 2018 Full School Day for Staff & Students
Friday, April 6, 2018 Full School Day for Staff & Students

Thank you for your continued support.

Sincerely,

H. Major Poteat, Ed.D.
Superintendent

Winslow Township Middle School Teacher Wins Grand Prize

Mr. Ross Cruz, Winslow Township Middle School Environmental STEM Teacher, won the 2016 Bernzomatic Grants Program Grand Prize. Mr. Cruz will receive:

‚Ä¢ a $15,000 Financial Grant, and
‚Ä¢ a donation of Bernzomatic products, not to exceed $1,500 in
retail value

Ms. Nicole Curtis, HGTV Host, and several Bernzomatic volunteers will visit the Middle School to make the official presentation.

The Winslow Township School District would like to congratulate Mr. Cruz and his Environmental STEM students for their hard work and success over the past two years. We would also like to thank the Middle School staff, and everyone in the Winslow Township community who voted in support of Mr. Cruz.

post_text:
2017 Winslow Township High School Girls' Track Team off to Great Start!

Congratulations to the Girls Track Team for a phenomenal start to the 2017 Indoor season. The ladies have dominated South Jersey with stellar performances across the board. The Girls Track Team began an action packed season by winning the novice division at the Egg Harbor Invitational Meet. They also earned the top seed in the 4x400 Relay at the Millrose Games. The 4x400 Relay Team of Iyianna Williams, Flora Ahiarakwe, Maryn Hess, and Shakira Dancy ran an impressive 3:57 which ranks them #1 in New Jersey and #5 in the Nation. We also congratulate Freshman Janeya Hammond for being ranked #1 in New Jersey and #9 in the Nation in the 300 meter dash.

post_text:
WTHS Marching Band Earns Top 10 Finish

On Saturday, October 29, 2016, the WTHS Marching Band competed at the Tournament of Bands Atlantic Coast Championship Competition. This final Competition of the season in the Tournament of Bands circuit took place at Central Dauphin HS in Harrisburg, PA and featured the best 16 Marching Bands (out of 38) in Group 2 from NJ, PA, DE, and NY. The WTHS Marching Band was seeded 11th entering the Championship. The Band finished in 6th place with a score of 89.1, winning Best Color Guard and placing 2nd in Percussion.

We would like to thank Mr. Parkhurst and the Marching Band for an award winning season.
